{"title_page": "Samen Stadium", "text_new": "{{More citations needed|date=December 2009}}\n{{Infobox venue \n| stadium_name      = Samen al-Aeme\n| fullname          = Samen al-Aeme Stadium\n| nickname          = \n| image             = Samen stadium mashhad.jpg\n| location          = [[Mashhad]], [[Iran]]\n| coordinates       = \n| broke_ground      = 1980\n| built             = 1980\u20131983\n| opened            = 1983\n| renovated         = 2004\n| expanded          = 2004\n| closed            =\n| demolished        =\n| owner             = [[Ministry of Sport and Youth (Iran)]] \n| operator          = [[F.C. Aboumoslem|Aboumoslem]]\n| surface           = Grass\n| Constructor       =\n| construction_cost =\n| architect         = \n| former_names      =\n| nicknames         =\n| tenants           = [[Siah Jamegan F.C.|Siah Jamegan]]<br>[[Padideh F.C.|Padideh]]\n| seating_capacity  = 35,000\n| dimensions        = \n}}\n\nThe '''Samen al-Aeme Stadium''' {{Lang-fa|\u0627\u0633\u062a\u0627\u062f\u064a\u0648\u0645 \u062b\u0627\u0645\u0646 \u0627\u0644\u0627\u0626\u0645\u0647 }} is a sport venue in the outskirts of [[Mashhad]], [[Iran]]. It is used by [[F.C. Aboumoslem|Aboumoslem]] and [[Padideh F.C.|Padideh]], two [[Iran]]ian [[Football (soccer)|football]] clubs from Mashhad. It is also used for track and field events, concerts and other local [[soccer|football]] teams. It has a capacity of 35,000 and the first phase of the project was completed in 2004 after more than 10 years. The latter phases will be completed in a few years time and will increase the stadium's capacity.\n\n==Notable matches==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: left;\"\n|-\n!Date\n!Team #1\n!Res.\n!Team #2\n!Competition\n!Attendance\n!Remarks\n|-\n|24 December 2004<ref>http://www.persianleague.com/history.html?view=teamfixtures&id=14&team=56&displayresults=yes&badges_ondisplay=yes</ref>||[[F.C. Aboomoslem|Abumoslem]]||style=\"text-align:center;\"|1\u20130||[[Persepolis F.C.|Persepolis]]||